1
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,526
-Goal!
-Goal!

2
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:14,908
-Goal!
-Goal!

3
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:17,368
Great job!

4
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:32,842
Honey.

5
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,720
It looks heavy. Let me carry that.

6
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,099
This is why I said I'd go with you.

7
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,352
Let's go and have a delicious meal.

8
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:49,901
Myeong-ju.

9
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:53,446
Hey.

10
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,489
You're here.

11
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:11,673
Dad!

12
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:16,678
-Dad!
-Yes, Hae-won.

13
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:21,099
-It's nice to be out, right?
-Yes.

14
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:23,893
Hurry up, Aunt!

15
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:25,770
Hurry up, honey!

16
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,165
Hey!

17
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:48,084
Who do you think you are?

18
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:51,588
Who do you think you are?

19
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:55,133
Why do you always do this to me?

20
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:56,593
Let go of me!

21
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,687
How dare you do that to me?

22
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:19,032
Hey! What gives you the right?

23
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:21,701
What gives you the right to hit my sister?

24
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:23,536
-Myeong-yeo!
-What gives you the right?

25
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,705
-You--
-What the hell do you know?

26
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:28,917
-No. Stop.
-You. Get over here!

27
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,209
-How dare you!
-Myeong-yeo.

28
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:33,046
-Myeong-yeo! Don't do it.
-How dare you!

29
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:35,798
-Stop it!
-What the hell?

30
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:38,092
Damn it!

31
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:39,636
Just get a divorce!

32
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,596
Divorce him!

33
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:45,099
What are you lacking
to have to live with a loser like him?

34
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:46,935
Myeong-ju!

35
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,188
-Divorce him. You don't deserve--
-Myeong-yeo!

36
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:51,773
No, stop!

37
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:53,149
-Stop it!
-Let go!

38
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,360
Who are you to tell her to get a divorce?

39
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,737
Who are you to tell her what to do?

40
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:32,939
Get out!

41
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,608
-Myeong-ju!
-I said, get out!

42
00:04:36,734 --> 00:04:37,610
Hey!

43
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:38,778
Damn it!

44
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,411
Myeong-ju! Get out!

45
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:47,578
I won't!

46
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:49,330
-No!
-I won't!

47
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:50,331
Get out!

48
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:52,166
Damn it!

49
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:57,630
-Why you…
-Get out of the way!

50
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:11,644
Are you nuts?

51
00:05:14,689 --> 00:05:16,024
No!

52
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:45,053
Myeong-ju.

53
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,947
Yes. Is this 911?

54
00:06:05,656 --> 00:06:06,824
There's been an accident.

55
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:09,952
Yes, that's the correct address.

56
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:12,622
Right. Yes, just now.

57
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,374
Yes.

58
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:20,088
Yes.

59
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,604
Get out.

60
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:41,526
Listen carefully.

61
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:43,945
Ju-hong is dead.

62
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:45,696
No.

63
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:49,117
Yes, he is. I checked.

64
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,036
I killed him.

65
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,538
No.

66
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:55,957
I killed him. It was me.

67
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:57,750
What?

68
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:58,835
Myeong-yeo.

69
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:01,963
Do you have cash with you?

70
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:07,135
No, I don't. No, I don't know.

71
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:12,974
Then just go straight out the gate
and get on the bus.

72
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:17,186
There are no security cameras here,
but there will be ones on the main street

73
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,896
in your neighborhood. Understand?

74
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,650
You will avoid them…

75
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:25,236
as you walk back to your place.

76
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:26,612
Got it?

77
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:30,408
Sim Myeong-yeo!

78
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,368
Pull yourself together!

79
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:36,205
Myeong-yeo, hurry up.

80
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:37,498
The shoes…

81
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,669
Myeong-yeo, here.

82
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:43,254
You can wear these shoes instead.

83
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:45,423
Put them on, Myeong-yeo!

84
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:51,137
Myeong-yeo.

85
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,514
Myeong-ju.

86
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:54,599
It's okay.

87
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:59,353
Take a shower once you get home.

88
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:00,897
Nothing happened.

89
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:03,524
It's okay. Nothing happened.

90
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:06,736
It's fine.

91
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,696
Nothing happened.

92
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:10,281
-Myeong-ju.
-You should go.

93
00:08:10,364 --> 00:08:12,492
-Hurry!
-Myeong-ju.

94
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,205
Hurry up and go.

95
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,834
Just go, Myeong-yeo.

96
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:24,337
Are you listening to me?

97
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:27,798
I said, just hurry up and go!

98
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:30,968
Go!

99
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:07,463
After you've taken a shower and a nap,

100
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:09,090
you will get a call.

101
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,150
Hello?

102
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:31,654
Yes, hello.

103
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:34,782
I'm investigator Gu Hyeon-tae
from the Paju police station.

104
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,161
Am I speaking to Ms. Sim Myeong-yeo?

105
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:45,668
Yes.

106
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,128
Yes.

107
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:52,091
I'm calling about Sim Myeong-ju.
Is she your older sister?

108
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:56,095
Yes.

109
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:01,142
So, her husband Mr. Mok Ju-hong

110
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,185
has passed away.

111
00:10:04,478 --> 00:10:05,980
It will be from the police

112
00:10:06,063 --> 00:10:10,026
to tell you that Ju-hong died
and I'm being interrogated as a suspect.

113
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:13,237
Yes. The thing is, your sister…

114
00:10:13,321 --> 00:10:15,573
I sentence the defendant Sim Myeong-ju

115
00:10:15,656 --> 00:10:17,992
to seven years in prison.

116
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,532
If I go to prison,

117
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,993
I can say I was running away
from my husband's abuse.

118
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:26,203
It will reduce my sentence.

119
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,496
But you can't.

120
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,550
You would have to stay in prison

121
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,510
for the rest of your life.

122
00:12:46,765 --> 00:12:50,311
That's why you can't be here.

123
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:56,692
Take Hae-won in and live with her.

124
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:25,679
What am I going to do?

125
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:27,973
What?

126
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,559
I don't think I'll ever forget…

127
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,439
the way you look right now.

128
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:03,759
I'm sleepy.

129
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:06,387
But I want to keep looking at you.

130
00:14:10,808 --> 00:14:12,643
You know, Eun-seop…

131
00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:15,813
Yes. I'm sleepy.

132
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:21,151
Are you?

133
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:24,321
Then go to sleep.

134
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:28,826
What were you going to say?

135
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,037
Nothing.

136
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:33,497
What is it?

137
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,837
Nothing. I'll tell you next time.

138
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:55,227
Mom!

139
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:56,937
Mom!

140
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,440
Mom!

141
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,235
Mom!

142
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,779
-Mom!
-What took you so long?

143
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,781
Your mom was desperately waiting for you.

144
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,283
Mom!

145
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:17,082
I pity the kid the most.

146
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:25,799
Mom!

147
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,066
What did you say?

148
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:44,360
I said…

149
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:48,197
I'll live here now
while taking care of Hae-won.

150
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:53,369
I mean,

151
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:55,955
don't you think

152
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,290
novels are pointless?

153
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:02,127
And Mom,

154
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:05,756
it turns out I'm not even that talented.

155
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,386
You're not talented?

156
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:11,637
No.

157
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:13,639
I don't have talent.

158
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,225
None.

159
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,894
So from now on,

160
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:22,731
I'll stay here with you and Hae-won,

161
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:24,692
and we can spend the rest of our lives--

162
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,050
Stay strong.

163
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:53,220
I told you. It's not your fault.

164
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:56,265
Myeong-ju.

165
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,058
If it wasn't for me,

166
00:16:59,601 --> 00:17:01,395
none of this would have happened.

167
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:07,067
Don't cry.

168
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,280
Go straight back home.

169
00:17:12,906 --> 00:17:14,033
Write your novel.

170
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:16,535
Go on dates.

171
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:18,996
And…

172
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,333
about Hae-won.

173
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,212
Try to spend…

174
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:31,050
a lot of time with her.

175
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:38,182
She's probably very lonely.

176
00:17:39,975 --> 00:17:41,852
-Myeong-ju.
-Listen, Myeong-yeo.

177
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:44,688
I'm…

178
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:48,484
I'm really…

179
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:55,324
SENDER: SIM MYEONG-JU

180
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:06,919
I'M FINE

181
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,111
Hey.

182
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:34,464
BOOKSTORE JOURNAL, NEW BLOG POST
THIS IS MY FIRST LOVE LETTER TO YOU

183
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:24,014
GOODNIGHT BOOKSTORE

184
00:20:35,817 --> 00:20:38,195
-Why are you coming from there?
-Gosh, you scared me.

185
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:40,197
At this time.

186
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:44,284
Well.

187
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:46,870
You're all grown now.

188
00:20:50,582 --> 00:20:51,875
So it's none of my business.

189
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:55,712
Where are you coming back from?

190
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,675
My friend passed away.

191
00:21:06,473 --> 00:21:09,810
I'm tired. Can we skip breakfast today?

192
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:11,603
Of course.

193
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:14,856
Or why don't I make something for us?

194
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:15,774
No, thanks.

195
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:19,861
Hey, you.

196
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:21,822
I heard…

197
00:21:23,365 --> 00:21:25,909
that people were impressed
by your cello performance.

198
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:27,869
Who told you?

199
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:29,538
Su-jeong.

200
00:21:30,497 --> 00:21:31,999
She said everyone raved about it.

201
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:33,917
I wouldn't go that far.

202
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:41,925
I wonder who took out all the sharp quills
from our family hedgehog.

203
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:43,885
What? What did you say?

204
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:46,305
A "hedgehog"? What?

205
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,556
It's a poetic expression.

206
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:52,185
Go inside.

207
00:21:53,353 --> 00:21:54,187
All right.

208
00:21:55,605 --> 00:21:56,898
It's cold. Come inside soon.

209
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:16,543
TRAVELS OF A SEPARATING COUPLE

210
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:24,176
Hae-won! Mok Hae-won, hurry.

211
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:25,093
Okay.

212
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:29,765
Come on, let's hurry!

213
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:10,347
Hey.

214
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:13,850
Looks like you have something fun there.

215
00:23:18,605 --> 00:23:22,025
What is this? Is it a piece of seaweed?

216
00:23:22,109 --> 00:23:23,318
They're stars.

217
00:23:23,985 --> 00:23:24,986
Stars?

218
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:28,156
I know what it is.
What do you take me for?

219
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:29,908
I'm a geek.

220
00:23:30,617 --> 00:23:32,327
You don't need to tell me that.

221
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,287
But you should know.

222
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:36,373
I'm a proud astronomy geek.

223
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:41,294
I see.

224
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:45,257
My heart flutters and I feel giddy
whenever I see the stars.

225
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:46,591
You're crazy.

226
00:23:46,675 --> 00:23:48,260
Then what about you?

227
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:50,095
What is that you have there?

228
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:51,763
So this…

229
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:55,058
This is something very precious to me.

230
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:56,059
I see.

231
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:57,853
So she means a lot to you.

232
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,146
What?

233
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:03,191
-She's pretty.
-That's not it. Not her.

234
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:04,568
You got it all wrong.

235
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:06,278
Then what is it?

236
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:10,907
Look here.

237
00:24:12,242 --> 00:24:14,828
You have to look closely
to see that she's the pretty one.

238
00:24:17,330 --> 00:24:18,874
-She's pretty too.
-She is, right?

239
00:24:18,957 --> 00:24:22,961
She's even prettier when she's eating.

240
00:24:23,587 --> 00:24:24,588
She has nice bangs.

241
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:26,715
Right, that and her overall style.

242
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:28,550
Hey, but seriously.

243
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:31,386
-Do you know the names of all of these?
-Yes.

244
00:24:31,469 --> 00:24:33,555
-And you look at this all day?
-Yes.

245
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:38,310
Mr. Cha.

246
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:40,979
Not now.

247
00:24:42,981 --> 00:24:45,567
The person you are trying to call
cannot be reached…

248
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:59,497
LOOK HERE. WHO DO YOU THINK
KILLED MY BROTHER-IN-LAW?

249
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:18,308
CRYBABY

250
00:25:18,391 --> 00:25:20,769
YOU HAVE 19 MISSED CALLS

251
00:25:41,414 --> 00:25:43,041
-Well…
-What is it?

252
00:25:43,124 --> 00:25:44,167
Forget it.

253
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:46,795
All right. Whatever.

254
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,258
By the way,

255
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:54,761
you look pretty good in those clothes.

256
00:25:57,430 --> 00:25:58,640
But I wear this every day.

257
00:25:58,723 --> 00:26:01,142
Looks nice.
Maybe because of your broad shoulders.

258
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:02,727
First I've ever heard that.

259
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:04,020
Are they really?

260
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:05,647
Yes. Broad like the Pacific Ocean.

261
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:11,069
I thought you said you didn't like me.

262
00:26:11,152 --> 00:26:13,530
I don't. It's all in the past.

263
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:17,158
But didn't you just say that I look good?

264
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:19,119
Yeong-su.

265
00:26:20,328 --> 00:26:23,707
If I say I don't like roses,
are they no longer beautiful?

266
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:27,085
No, they're still beautiful
regardless of how I feel.

267
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:29,713
That's what this is.

268
00:26:29,796 --> 00:26:32,590
The fact that you have broad shoulders
and look good in your clothes

269
00:26:32,674 --> 00:26:34,009
has nothing to do with me.

270
00:26:34,092 --> 00:26:36,803
My feelings were in the past,
but you look great now.

271
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:38,430
And that's just the way it is.

272
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:43,393
Is the bookstore far from here?

273
00:26:43,476 --> 00:26:46,855
Yes, so you'd better keep up with me.

274
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:50,775
It feels different
to meet in the afternoon.

275
00:26:50,859 --> 00:26:51,693
Yes, it does.

276
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:55,405
