00:33:16,411 --> 00:33:19,872
You know, I've always considered it

408
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:23,292
as something like the fox
in The Little Prince.

409
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:27,839
Something that exists
but is very hard to believe in

410
00:33:27,922 --> 00:33:29,882
because it doesn't seem believable.

411
00:33:29,966 --> 00:33:32,927
Well Mr. Bae, he really is
the top student at the school.

412
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:34,262
He always gets good grades.

413
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:37,348
But Hwi, aren't you younger than him?

414
00:33:37,432 --> 00:33:38,808
Yes, I am.

415
00:33:38,891 --> 00:33:40,560
-But why…
-Why does she talk informally?

416
00:33:40,643 --> 00:33:42,562
Because she doesn't like using honorifics.

417
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:44,272
Yes.

418
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:48,317
Then why do you use them with me?

419
00:33:49,235 --> 00:33:51,237
Now, you have to think carefully.

420
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:56,242
Did I really speak formally to you
every time you and I spoke?

421
00:33:56,325 --> 00:33:59,662
Are you sure that's not just
how you think it's been?

422
00:33:59,746 --> 00:34:03,458
If you look back, I might have
been talking informally to you all along.

423
00:34:06,753 --> 00:34:07,712
What in the world…

424
00:34:11,132 --> 00:34:14,677
But Yeong-su,
why do you smile every time she talks?

425
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:17,889
