And I was afraid you might jump into it.

539
00:47:54,454 --> 00:47:57,332
Hello, Ms. Sim. I'm Im Eun-seop,
the son of Mr. Im Jong-pil--

540
00:48:00,627 --> 00:48:02,921
Yes, Myeong-yeo.

541
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:07,759
It's just that I'm at this place.

542
00:48:08,969 --> 00:48:10,721
Do you have some time right now?

543
00:48:19,021 --> 00:48:20,105
No, the thing is…

544
00:48:38,874 --> 00:48:41,084
CAMPING SITE

545
00:49:39,267 --> 00:49:40,936
Yes, I'm almost there.

546
00:49:43,146 --> 00:49:44,272
Please drive faster.

547
00:49:44,856 --> 00:49:46,274
I'm driving as fast as I can.

548
00:49:47,192 --> 00:49:48,985
But why did she come all the way here?

549
00:49:56,785 --> 00:49:58,704
I called your aunt,

550
00:50:10,173 --> 00:50:11,216
but I was still afraid.

551
00:50:13,927 --> 00:50:15,220
I was afraid you might die.

552
00:50:20,308 --> 00:50:21,309
That you might die.

553
00:50:26,982 --> 00:50:27,816
Hey, Mok Hae-won!

554
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:30,026
Mok Hae-won!

555
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:31,862
Come here. Let's go.

556
00:50:31,945 --> 00:50:34,656
-You're hurting me.
-Are you insane?

557
00:50:36,575 --> 00:50:37,868
What were you thinking?

558
00:50:56,636 --> 00:50:57,846
And I think…

559
00:51:01,725 --> 00:51:05,270
that was our first autumn trip together.

560
00:51:10,150 --> 00:51:11,318
I escaped!

561
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:16,406
Good job.

562
00:51:17,324 --> 00:51:18,533
It was so hard to get out.

563
00:51:18,617 --> 00:51:20,035
My aunt wasn't sleeping

564
00:51:20,118 --> 00:51:22,412
so I had to wait
until things quieted down.

565
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:28,001
-What were you doing?
-Nothing.

566
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:29,920
What is it?

567
00:51:30,754 --> 00:51:32,589
-Tell me.
-Wait.

568
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:34,424
What's going on?

569
00:51:35,801 --> 00:51:37,511
-Just, it's nothing.
-What is it?

570
00:51:38,720 --> 00:51:40,263
Now I'm getting upset.

571
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:43,600
I was just ordering something online…

572
00:51:44,768 --> 00:51:47,270
You know, online shopping.

573
00:51:47,354 --> 00:51:48,939
Okay. Then let me see it.

574
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:53,318
-Gosh, seriously? This is upsetting.
-It's not what you think.

575
00:51:54,569 --> 00:51:55,695
I'm upset.

576
00:51:55,779 --> 00:51:56,988
But Hae-won, it's nothing.

577
00:51:57,072 --> 00:51:58,657
I get jealous easily.

578
00:51:59,741 --> 00:52:01,117
To chop wood,

579
00:52:02,494 --> 00:52:04,371
you have to relax, even your arms.

580
00:52:08,124 --> 00:52:11,628
Place the edge of the ax along the grain
because that's where the wood splits.

581
00:52:12,170 --> 00:52:13,255
Now, look.

582
00:52:13,338 --> 00:52:14,881
-Can you stand back?
-Okay.

583
00:52:26,977 --> 00:52:29,729
This is how not to do it.
I did that on purpose to show you.

584
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:32,482
-Okay.
-All right.

585
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:34,860
So this is how you do it.

586
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:38,154
Like I said,

587
00:52:38,238 --> 00:52:40,198
-find where the wood wants to split.
-Okay.

588
00:52:41,408 --> 00:52:42,325
All right.

589
00:52:49,791 --> 00:52:52,794
Gosh. There's a chip on the blade.

590
00:52:54,462 --> 00:52:55,297
It's chipped.

591
00:52:56,756 --> 00:52:57,591
Want to try?

592
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,426
Me? Can I?

593
00:52:59,509 --> 00:53:00,886
-Of course.
-Really?

594
00:53:01,469 --> 00:53:02,929
It probably won't work, though.

595
00:53:03,013 --> 00:53:04,764
Right. You couldn't do it either.

596
00:53:05,724 --> 00:53:08,727
I've tried doing this
only for fun back home.

597
00:53:08,810 --> 00:53:10,437
Just to let off some steam.

598
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:12,981
-Place your hand over here.
-Okay.

599
00:53:13,940 --> 00:53:16,067
And hold this at the back.

600
00:53:16,151 --> 00:53:19,279
-Aim and then chop.
-Okay.

601
00:53:19,362 --> 00:53:22,282
But you were swinging it
all the way back, like this.

602
00:53:22,365 --> 00:53:24,075
That's only for experts.

603
00:53:24,159 --> 00:53:26,202
-I see. And this is for beginners?
-Yes.

604
00:53:26,286 --> 00:53:28,830
-Yes. Just drop your ax from here.
-Okay.

605
00:53:31,166 --> 00:53:32,000
Try this.

606
00:53:34,044 --> 00:53:35,629
So I should do this, and then…

607
00:53:39,257 --> 00:53:40,091
Like this?

608
00:53:44,763 --> 00:53:45,680
How did you do that?

609
00:53:47,223 --> 00:53:48,892
I did what you taught me.

610
00:53:48,975 --> 00:53:50,185
I see.

611
00:53:51,269 --> 00:53:52,312
Was it your first time?

612
00:53:55,607 --> 00:53:58,151
But now my shoulders are sore.

613
00:53:58,234 --> 00:54:00,695
I think I've used up all my strength.
Can you do it?

614
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:01,613
All right.

615
00:54:02,614 --> 00:54:04,491
I showed you how not to do it.

616
00:54:05,241 --> 00:54:06,910
I'll really show you how it's done.

617
00:54:07,535 --> 00:54:09,913
I'm waiting. Go ahead.

618
00:54:14,250 --> 00:54:15,460
-Now watch.
-Okay.

619
00:54:16,795 --> 00:54:18,463
-It's dangerous, stand back.
-I will.

620
00:54:32,811 --> 00:54:33,645
I give up.

621
00:54:34,270 --> 00:54:35,105
Eun-seop.

622
00:54:35,855 --> 00:54:36,690
Eun-seop!

623
00:55:01,881 --> 00:55:02,882
Mrs. Kim!

624
00:55:02,966 --> 00:55:04,968
BOGUK MILL, VARIOUS OILS

625
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:06,886
Mrs. Kim!

626
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:10,724
You're too early. The crushed red pepper
won't be ready until later.

627
00:55:10,807 --> 00:55:12,684
Hey, did you hear the news?

628
00:55:12,767 --> 00:55:14,602
Min-jeong went missing!

629
00:55:15,103 --> 00:55:18,565
You know who she is, right?
She's the one who recently passed

630
00:55:18,648 --> 00:55:19,733
the civil service exam!

631
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:21,860
The third daughter
of that red-roof house at the roundabout?

632
00:55:21,943 --> 00:55:24,654
That's right. She went missing.

633
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:26,072
I'm back.

634
00:55:26,656 --> 00:55:30,160
-That's terrible.
-So the whole town is on the lookout.

635
00:55:30,243 --> 00:55:32,746
Jong-pil's son, Eun-seop, rushed over.

636
00:55:33,246 --> 00:55:34,497
Why did he do that?

637
00:55:34,581 --> 00:55:36,875
Who knows? But he's the one…

638
00:55:37,959 --> 00:55:39,753
who used to live in the mountains.

639
00:55:39,836 --> 00:55:43,214
So he was asked to search for her
in the area where she went missing.

640
00:55:43,298 --> 00:55:45,175
Goodness. I hope they find her.

641
00:55:45,258 --> 00:55:47,635
Yes, I hope so too.

642
00:55:47,719 --> 00:55:49,471
And the weather is so cold.

643
00:55:49,554 --> 00:55:52,223
Let's head over there
to see if we can help.

644
00:55:52,307 --> 00:55:54,059
-Let's go.
-All right.

645
00:55:54,976 --> 00:55:57,562
-Why did you come here and not home?
-What?

646
00:55:57,645 --> 00:56:00,732
Wait. Let's bring over
some hot coffee in a tumbler.

647
00:56:00,815 --> 00:56:03,985
Do you have any Korean rice cakes?
Roasted soybean would be nice.

648
00:56:52,992 --> 00:56:55,954
GOODNIGHT BOOKSTORE

649
00:57:04,295 --> 00:57:05,547
What should I do?

650
00:57:07,257 --> 00:57:08,091
What is it?

651
00:57:10,343 --> 00:57:11,928
I really like you.

652
00:57:13,638 --> 00:57:14,472
What do I do?

653
00:57:30,363 --> 00:57:31,197
How about you?

654
00:57:33,658 --> 00:57:34,492
Likewise.

655
00:57:49,549 --> 00:57:50,758
It's true, Eun-seop.

656
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:54,971
Even the small and insignificant
have feelings.

657
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:07,066
What do you want to drink? I'll get…

658
00:58:07,150 --> 00:58:08,943
What's up?

659
00:58:11,404 --> 00:58:12,739
I thought it might be urgent.

660
00:58:12,822 --> 00:58:14,908
Is something going on?

661
00:58:16,367 --> 00:58:18,244
TRAVELS OF A SEPARATING COUPLE

662
00:58:18,828 --> 00:58:19,871
Here.

663
00:58:21,789 --> 00:58:23,041
Feel free to start reading.

664
00:58:47,732 --> 00:58:49,817
CONTACTS

665
00:58:49,901 --> 00:58:51,236
IM EUN-SEOP

666
00:58:52,695 --> 00:58:53,613
I just want you…

667
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:57,659
to know.

668
00:59:01,162 --> 00:59:02,539
In any way possible,

669
00:59:04,457 --> 00:59:06,084
whatever it takes,

670
00:59:08,836 --> 00:59:09,963
I want you…

671
00:59:11,756 --> 00:59:13,424
-Let's do it!
-No, I'm okay.

672
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:15,009
Please, just this once.

673
00:59:15,885 --> 00:59:17,845
You really don't want to?
When it's with me?

674
00:59:17,929 --> 00:59:19,138
But you said you use a hot iron.

675
00:59:19,222 --> 00:59:22,058
No. That was clearly a joke.
Did you believe that?

676
00:59:22,141 --> 00:59:24,394
-Hang on.
-Let's do it.

677
00:59:28,147 --> 00:59:31,568
KIM BO-YEONG

678
00:59:37,949 --> 00:59:39,158
…to know that.

679
01:00:13,735 --> 01:00:16,821
BOOKSTORE JOURNAL
A GOODNIGHT BOOKSTORE PRIVATE BLOG POST

680
01:00:16,904 --> 01:00:18,531
POSTED BY SEOP

681
01:00:19,198 --> 01:00:23,077
This is my first love letter to you.

682
01:00:23,870 --> 01:00:28,082
That day, on the other side of the window,

683
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:33,087
I saw you with a hurt look on your face
that was just like mine.

684
01:00:33,921 --> 01:00:38,217
I should go. No, I shouldn't.
I'd feel bad.

685
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:43,222
I forgot all that was in my head
and followed you.

686
01:00:43,848 --> 01:00:45,683
A town with many persimmon trees.

687
01:00:45,767 --> 01:00:48,227
It had clear water flowing
from the Nakdong River.

688
01:00:48,978 --> 01:00:53,107
And I was afraid you might jump into it.

689
01:00:53,691 --> 01:00:56,235
I called your aunt,
but I was still afraid.

690
01:00:56,319 --> 01:00:58,112
I was afraid you might die.

691
01:00:58,863 --> 01:01:04,243
And I think that was
our first autumn trip together.

692
01:01:08,831 --> 01:01:10,500
I want you to come and rescue me.

693
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:12,168
I'll wait.

694
01:01:12,752 --> 01:01:13,586
-Hello, Eun-sil.
-What the…

695
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:15,463
-So you're going to a nice place later?
-What?

696
01:01:15,546 --> 01:01:17,006
I'll be there too.

697
01:01:17,090 --> 01:01:18,424
I'm Irene?

698
01:01:18,508 --> 01:01:21,427
Could you tell me how far you got?

699
01:01:21,511 --> 01:01:23,262
Can you tell me it's all a lie?

700
01:01:23,346 --> 01:01:24,931
I've lost my light.

701
01:01:25,014 --> 01:01:26,474
Now I have nothing.

702
01:01:26,557 --> 01:01:27,600
I wish you a good life.

703
01:01:27,684 --> 01:01:30,812
I understand you'll be leaving
this place someday.

704
01:01:30,895 --> 01:01:33,773
However, I hope your heart
won't feel too heavy.

705
01:01:33,856 --> 01:01:35,858
I'm preparing for it all.

706
01:01:38,486 --> 01:01:43,491
